Passive ability, costs 5 points<br>
<br>
Training this skill turns the mage's nukes into lures. It does not increase the damage a nuke does, but it bases all resist checks from the same rules as wizard lure spells.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Came up with this while reflecting on a night spent nuking glimmer drakes in ToV for 245 - 350 with SoFB. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
This has the indirect bonus of possibly elevating mages back to the #2 nuker position above druids, simply by virtue of doing more damage over time thanks to fewer resists.<br>
<br>
Thoughts? <p><font face="Verdana">
<b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=24658" target=_blank>Sambus Veneficus</a></b><br> Arch Mage of Ak'anon<br> Mithaniel Marr Server</font><br><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uarchangyl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Archangyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(8/20/02 6:42:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=305.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fantasygamer.net/ff9/artwork/bomb.jpg  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Just an AA idea I had.</span><hr size=1> Turning ALL of the nukes into lures might be a little too powerful, maybe just the non-magic based nukes. For something different you could add levels too it. First point effects all spells level 20 and under, second point 40 and under, third point levels 52 and under.<br>
<br>
Also, it would be more plausable if this were an activated ability that would effect the next nuke you cast with a refresh time of 72 minutes of something. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uarchangyl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Archangyl</A> at: 8/20/02 6:58:10 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umaigedenugget.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maige Denugget</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#333333>(8/20/02 6:43:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=305.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Just an AA idea I had.</span><hr size=1> Interesting idea, but it's gonna be a NO GO... <br>
<br>
Wizards pay for having lures by having them be inefficient manawise.  To give magicians an ability that allows us to passively turn our efficient nukes into lures, while wizards have to use inefficient lures, is totally way off base.<br>
<br>
I like the idea of looking for ways to up our nuke damage.  This isn't the way tho.<br>
<br>
- Maige <p><b>Maige Denugget</b><br>Master of the Elements<br>
Magician of the GNOMISH kind<br><br>

