I thought about levels, but, eh.  Buying into levels is annoying.  Plus I don't really think anyone would want to buy the first 2 levels if they only worked for nukes lower than level 40 since nobody who's investing in class abilities is going to use nukes that are such low level anyway.<br>
<br>
Edit:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Also, it would be more plausable if this were an activated ability that would effect the next nuke you cast with a refresh time of 72 minutes of something.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I don't really think there'd be a point to purchasing this skill if you can only cast one nuke that has a better chance of landing every 72 minutes.  You might as well use the nuke mana to make another mod rod for a wizard to use instead.  That would really be too limiting.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>    Wizards pay for having lures by having them be inefficient manawise. To give magicians an ability that allows us to passively turn our efficient nukes into lures, while wizards have to use inefficient lures, is totally way off base.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I disagree.  I recently read <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=19479.topic">a thread on Graffe's about lures</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, and some of the wizards commented that since the resistance patch they don't really bother with using lures anymore.  Obviously they still have their uses, but apparently they're not as crucial as they used to be.<br>
<br>
This ability is relatively well balanced by a couple things:<br>
1- Wizards are given lures at various levels which they can promptly scribe into their spellbook and use on the spot, which is the way it should be.  In contrast, this is a class ability which requires significant points investment to get to and earn.  If it would be fairer to require a pre-requisite from arch abilities, that's cool.<br>
<br>
2- We still would not be able to touch anything that requires cold-based nukes.  This would however allow us to have an easier time nuking what we already can, and would open up a few more targets for us that are currently &quot;weak&quot; to fire/magic, but which still require lures of those resist types. <p><font face="Verdana">
<b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=24658" target=_blank>Sambus Veneficus</a></b><br> Arch Mage of Ak'anon<br> Mithaniel Marr Server</font><br><br></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usambus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sambus</A> at: 8/20/02 7:14:35 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uarchangyl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Archangyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(8/21/02 3:03:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=305.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fantasygamer.net/ff9/artwork/bomb.jpg  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Just an AA idea I had.</span><hr size=1> Thinking about it again,<br>
