<br>
However, Wizards get a natural lure bonus to all their spells once they break Level 35. No other class gets this.<br>
<br>
If this skill was given to us, it would have to be a lesser lure effect with a much higher possibility of resists than the wizard lures before they were made unresistable on Test. (21st Aug 2002)<br>
<br>
Instead, the AA ability could be akin to the level 35 lure bonus that wizards get.<br>
<br>
I think that Magicians should get a lesser lure line of DDs 50+ (say, 4 new spells) baring in mind they they wouldn't even be 1:2 manna/damage ratio!<br>
<br>
Even if we had them, we'd still be rod machines. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ushadextinkerdink.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadex Tinkerdink</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 199<br> <font color=#333333>(8/21/02 2:25:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=305.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Not too keen on this idea...</span><hr size=1> Would be neat, but also a coding nightmare, and that whole efficiency thing.<br>
